com.ibm.team.repository.common.query.ast

Interface IAggregateFunction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ISelectionElement

    public interface IAggregateFunction
extends ISelectionElement
    Represents a query aggregate function. Aggregation function performs a computation on a set of values and returns a single value. AVG, MIN, MAX, SUM and COUNT are the supported aggregate functions. Aggregate functions can be created using the creator methods defined in a IDataQuery. For example, avg function on a query model field can be created using IDataQuery.avg(IField)
    Since:
    0.5
    See Also:
    IDataQuery
